This pain hurt. This time is really really hurt. I left my heart locked up for years. To protect it,  to protect me….until someone had a key. They made my days shine brighter, I felt loved, I felt safe…..until I didn’t. The screaming. The throwing of objects. The leaving me to walk 10 miles home on a highway. The countless drunken nights passing out at 7pm then made me walk on egg shells the next day when hungover, or as it was said “tired.” The shaming. The name calling. The pouring of beer on me. The telling me IM embarrassing. The nitpicking. The lies. It  ALL FUKKKKKKKING HURT, and extra this time; I thought I had grown and healed. But your pretty wrapped package got me…You invited me, you wanted me to stay, you wanted me to travel with you, you wanted me to have a break from being the MF’N BOSS I AM!!!! You told me you loved me. Then you made me feel as if I wasn’t good enough, or worthy of ANY of it. Well guess what mf’er. I’m BACK on top. I’m STILL sober. I am BEAUTIFUL. I shine. I am every growing. I am KIND. We take all we can, until we can’t. I am not perfect, but I am self aware. Anyway. There’s a piece of my most recent times I LOVE me. Those cries I had, they’re gone now. My spirit is back, and you can watch me flourish. Love is patient, love is kind.  I AM WORTHY.

I went down a YouTube rabbit hole to find my first ever video, it’s so depressing! I’m so freaking grateful for the last 11 years! From deeeeply unhealthy habits, to a non drinking mostly low carb queen! Tons of research, trial and error, gains and losses of all kinds….that’s what got me here. I still am noooo fitness guru, I will eat a family size bag of salt n vinegar chips no prob, if I want. I will stop the daily gym, for months at a time….I don’t recommend that one, my mental health is happier with quality daily physical activity. Point being, over time I really implemented better food, and physical choices.  Started mental health work too. I  didn’t deny myself my favorite foods, but I did learn how to make them mostly protein based…that helped. I still get fast food and have ice cream and pizza…..and here I am 11 years later and feelin pretty great. I have some physical goals I am working on now, and you’ll continue to see that.  I don’t make long captions, as I just feel I’m rambling butttttt. Point is. You are number one, you have to learn to not just like…but love you. I was so lost 11 years ago, and not sure what I’m doing today either….but I love me now. I am learning and practicing daily how to do that. I do NOT have it all figured out, but I hope you can scroll away with this: you’re worth making some hard choices to better yourself; you deserve it!!!!!! #happiness

I’m happy, and thriving..just some clouds lately. But I know why. 12/28/1994 the day my dad chose his path. I have no voice mails, text wasn’t a thing, I hardly have anything to remind me of him. It’s 2023 now and I’m about to be older than my father ever was. It’s so fucking weird. It’s a depression I’ve sat with for months now, but knowing I’m about the literal day in age as when he ended his life is boiling my emotions. I have no doubt my future is bright, but I want to turn 39, so this cloud goes away. I’ve done things he loved, and will continue to. I see him everywhere, I’m not angry anymore, usually. I wonder if I sit outside so much, so I can be near him. Idk. This is just a ramble. Grief is strange. You’re never alone, but I understand you feeling lonely. I love you, please stay. #suicidepreventionmonth #suicide #survivorofsuicide #grief #birthdays #griefjourney #griefawareness #iloveyou 🎀

The secret to keeping the weight off. 
Sure you can eat well, workout, but if you don’t do the damn MENTAL work, you’re never gonna find happiness and always fall back on unhealthy coping mechanisms…So, these are my tips. ⬇️⬇️⬇️
1. Keep the consistency in the gym, and kitchen, yes. 
2. Seek therapy, no shame in mental help professional game
3. Give yourself some grace, this all takes time and training! Mental and physical
